Class UrgentProcessor

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Thread
      xxl.core.pipes.processors.Processor
          xxl.core.pipes.processors.UrgentProcessor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Runnable, MetaDataManageable<Object,Object>, MetaDataProvider<CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>>
Direct Known Subclasses:
HeartbeatGenerator, PeriodicEvaluationMetaDataHandler.PeriodicEvaluationProcessor, SourceProcessor
public abstract class UrgentProcessor
extends Processor

A Processor that has to be scheduled with high priority by a Scheduler. That means, that such a processor is not allowed to be blocked over a longer time by the scheduler. Processors for sources will usually be of this kind SourceProcessor.

Since:
1.1
See Also:
Scheduler, Processor, SourceProcessor

UrgentProcessor

public UrgentProcessor(long period)
Creates a new urgent processor. If a scheduler is set, this processor will register to this scheduler and set its scheduling priority to the norm scheduling priority defined by the used scheduler.

Parameters:
period - Delay between two successive process calls (in milliseconds).
